Package ohos.media.camera.device

Class FrameStateCallback

  • java.lang.Object
    • ohos.media.camera.device.FrameStateCallback

  • public abstract class FrameStateCallback
extends Object
    Provides callbacks for the frame processing states.

    As input parameters of Camera#configure(CameraConfig), the callbacks are used to obtain the frame processing states.

    Since:
    1
    SystemCapability
    SystemCapability.Multimedia#CAMERA

      • onCaptureTriggerStarted

        public void onCaptureTriggerStarted​(Camera camera,
                                    int captureTriggerId,
                                    long firstFrameNumber)
        Called when frame capture is started for a trigger.

        A trigger can start one or more frame capture actions, and this callback identifies the start of this time of triggering.

        Parameters:
        camera - Indicates the camera.
        captureTriggerId - Indicates a trigger ID.
        firstFrameNumber - Indicates the frame number of the first frame in this capture.
        Since:
        1

      • onCaptureTriggerFinished

        public void onCaptureTriggerFinished​(Camera camera,
                                     int captureTriggerId,
                                     long lastFrameNumber)
        Called when a triggered frame capture action is finished.

        A trigger can start one or more frame capture actions, and this callback identifies the end of this time of triggering.

        Parameters:
        camera - Indicates the camera.
        captureTriggerId - Indicates a trigger ID.
        lastFrameNumber - Indicates the frame number of the last frame in this capture.

        The last frame number can be -1, indicating that no frame is captured.

        Since:
        3

      • onCaptureTriggerInterrupted

        public void onCaptureTriggerInterrupted​(Camera camera,
                                        int captureTriggerId)
        Called when a triggered frame capture action is stopped in advance.

        A trigger can start one or more frame capture actions at a time, and this callback identifies this time of triggering.

        Parameters:
        camera - Indicates the camera.
        captureTriggerId - Indicates a trigger ID.
        Since:
        3
